<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E807513B7EC1FDF33EF0FCB9" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE807513B7EC1FDF33EF0FCB9" blockId="7.[151,761,551,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7EC1FDF33E4CFDD9" bold="true" box="[151,269,551,574]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male body length 
<quantity id="4C80279EE807513B7FB1FDF33D0FFDD9" box="[487,590,551,574]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="3.05">3.05 mm</quantity>
. Antennomeres 9–11 enlarged and forming club, antennomeres 9 and 10 each with small tubercle at apex and base, respectively. Horn-like metaventral processes long, in lateral view narrowing apically. Protrochanter with tiny ventral spine, mesotrochanter with acute ventral spine; mesofemur with small tooth at middle. Median lobe of aedeagus slightly asymmetrical dorso-ventrally; parameres elongate; endophallus composed of spine-like structures and a single sclerite. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E807513B7EC1FCB33EC7F9B9" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE807513B7EC1FCB33DB9F9D9" blockId="7.[151,761,551,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7EC1FCB33E2DFC99" bold="true" box="[151,364,871,894]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
Description. 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7F64FCB33E2DFC99" bold="true" box="[306,364,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Male</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134396FEE807513B7FD6FCB33E9FFC99" box="[384,478,871,894]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[151,182,2063,2082]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,843,2025]" captionTargetId="figure-377@5.[152,1436,835,2033]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 4. Dorsal habitus of Pselaphodes males. A – P. banphabat sp. nov.; B – P. dalatensis sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037476/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="4C80279EE807513B7CDDFCB33DB2FC99" box="[651,755,871,894]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="3.05">3.05 mm</quantity>
, Head approximately as long as wide, HL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE807513B7C0AFC533DFEFC79" box="[604,703,903,926]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8999999999999995" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="0.59">0.59 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE807513B7EC1FC733FBCFC59" box="[151,253,935,958]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.699999999999999" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="0.57">0.57 mm</quantity>
; eyes prominent, each composed of about 44 facets. Antennomeres 9–11 (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE807513B7F87FC133D69FC39" box="[465,552,967,990]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,2008,2027]" captionTargetBox="[256,1336,665,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-262@6.[251,1336,665,1980]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 5. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes banphabat sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – metatrochanter and metafemur; G – sternite 7 (IX); H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, F; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.1 mm in G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
) enlarged and forming distinct club, antennomere 9 with a round tubercle at apex, antennomere 10 with similar but larger tubercle at base. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE807513B7F31FBF33EFBFBD9" box="[359,442,1063,1086]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,2008,2027]" captionTargetBox="[256,1336,665,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-262@6.[251,1336,665,1980]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 5. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes banphabat sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – metatrochanter and metafemur; G – sternite 7 (IX); H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, F; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.1 mm in G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
) as long as wide, PL and PW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE807513B7EC1FB933FB8FBB9" box="[151,249,1095,1118]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8999999999999995" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="0.59">0.59 mm</quantity>
, roundly narrowing apically at apical 2/5. Elytra much broader than long, EL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE807513B7FB9FBB33D13FB99" box="[495,594,1127,1150]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.299999999999999" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="0.83">0.83 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE807513B7CC6FBB33DB4FB99" box="[656,757,1127,1150]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="1.05">1.05 mm</quantity>
. Horn-like metaventral processes (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE807513B7FA8FB533D0EFB79" box="[510,591,1159,1182]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,2008,2027]" captionTargetBox="[256,1336,665,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-262@6.[251,1336,665,1980]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 5. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes banphabat sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – metatrochanter and metafemur; G – sternite 7 (IX); H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, F; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.1 mm in G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
) long, in lateral view narrowing apically. Protrochanter (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE807513B7C6AFB733DCFFB59" box="[572,654,1191,1214]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,2008,2027]" captionTargetBox="[256,1336,665,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-262@6.[251,1336,665,1980]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 5. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes banphabat sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – metatrochanter and metafemur; G – sternite 7 (IX); H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, F; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.1 mm in G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
) with tiny spine at ventral margin, profemur simple; mesotrochanter (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE807513B7EC9FB333FAEFB19" box="[159,239,1255,1278]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,2008,2027]" captionTargetBox="[256,1336,665,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-262@6.[251,1336,665,1980]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 5. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes banphabat sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – metatrochanter and metafemur; G – sternite 7 (IX); H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, F; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.1 mm in G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
) with acute ventral spine, mesofemur with small tooth at middle; metatrochanter and metafemur (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE807513B7CF6FAD33DB1FAF9" box="[672,752,1287,1310]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,2008,2027]" captionTargetBox="[256,1336,665,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-262@6.[251,1336,665,1980]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 5. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes banphabat sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – metatrochanter and metafemur; G – sternite 7 (IX); H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, F; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.1 mm in G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
) simple. Abdomen broad at base and narrowed posteriorly, AL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE807513B7E97FA933E62FAB9" box="[193,291,1351,1374]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="0.98">0.98 mm</quantity>
, AW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE807513B7F08FA933E80FAB9" box="[350,449,1351,1374]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="1.05">1.05 mm</quantity>
; tergite 1 (IV) longest, about 2.5 times as long as tergite V; sternite 7 (IX) (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE807513B7C23FAB33D89FA99" box="[629,712,1383,1406]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,2008,2027]" captionTargetBox="[256,1336,665,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-262@6.[251,1336,665,1980]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 5. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes banphabat sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – metatrochanter and metafemur; G – sternite 7 (IX); H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, F; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.1 mm in G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5G</figureCitation>
) hemi-membranous, semi-ellipse. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE807513B7C05FA533DFCFA79" box="[595,701,1415,1438]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,2008,2027]" captionTargetBox="[256,1336,665,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-262@6.[251,1336,665,1980]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 5. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes banphabat sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – metatrochanter and metafemur; G – sternite 7 (IX); H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, F; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.1 mm in G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5H–J</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4C80279EE807513B7C9FFA533F81FA59" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8999999999999995" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="0.59">0.59 mm</quantity>
long; median lobe dorso-ventrally slightly asymmetric; parameres elongate, broadening to near apices, then greatly narrowed at apices, each paramere with one long apical seta; endophallus composed of numerous spine-like structures, one membranous part, and one forked sclerite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE807513B7EE3F9933EC7F9B9" blockId="7.[151,761,551,1822]" box="[181,390,1607,1630]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7EE3F9933E4EF9B9" bold="true" box="[181,271,1607,1630]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7EE3F9933E49F9B9" bold="true" box="[181,264,1607,1630]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E807513B7EC1F9B33DB8F959" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE807513B7EC1F9B33DB8F959" blockId="7.[151,761,551,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7EC1F9B33E37F999" bold="true" box="[151,374,1639,1662]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
The new species is quite distinctive in the form of the male antennal clubs, which leads to a ready separation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E807513B7F34F9733EAEF959" authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[354,495,1703,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="banphabat">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7F34F9733E33F959" box="[354,370,1703,1726]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7F28F9733EAEF959" box="[382,495,1703,1726]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">banphabat</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E807513B7EC1F9133DA2F919" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE807513B7EC1F9133DA2F919" blockId="7.[151,761,551,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7EC1F9133E5AF939" bold="true" box="[151,283,1735,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after the 
<typeStatus id="54C334D9E807513B7C9EF9133DB6F939" box="[712,759,1735,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
locality, Ban Phabat. The name is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E807513B7EC1F8D33D41F8F9" box="[151,512,1799,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE807513B7EC1F8D33D41F8F9" blockId="7.[151,761,551,1822]" box="[151,512,1799,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
